  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0da7\u0dda \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0da9\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0da7 10 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Covid has increased by 10 percent in the country",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "As the spread of covid in the country has increased by about 10 percent, people should be careful by following the health guidelines properly, Dr. Anwar Hamdani, co-ordinator and director of technology services of the Ministry of Health, told Lankadeepa.",
        "He also mentioned that between 4 and 5 Covid deaths are reported daily.",
        "The covid co-ordinator said that no matter what outbreak occurs, the country or any other place will not be affected at all. He also stated that since the country has optimal immunity for covid, it is possible to manage covid patients at home to a large extent.",
        "Mr. Anwar Hamdani also said that people are requested to follow the Covid health guidelines properly to prevent the spread of Covid.",
        "The doctor mentioned that people who have not received the prescribed doses of vaccines should immediately get vaccinated and all the necessary facilities have been provided for that.",
        "He added that the spread of Covid in the country should not be underestimated."
      ],
